= SDL_ShowCursor =
Use this function to toggle whether or not the cursor is shown.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_ShowCursor(int toggle)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''toggle'''
|1 to show the cursor, 0 to hide it, -1 to query the current state
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 1 if the cursor is shown, or 0 if the cursor is hidden, <<Color2(green, or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information)>>.

